Sentencas: This study investigates the influence of the sintering temperature on the properties of the screen-printed anode of the La0.6Sr1.4MnO4 (LSMO4) Ruddlesden-Popper (R-P) perovskite for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell applications.
Titulo: Influence of sintering temperature on the properties of the screen-printed anode of the LSMO4 Ruddlesden-Popper perovskite for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
Influence of sintering temperature on the properties of the screen-printed anode of the LSMO4 Ruddlesden-Popper perovskite for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: precursor powders with a K2NiF4-type (I4/mmm space group) tetragonal structure, density of 5.823 g/cm3, and specific surface area of 2.121 m2/g were successfully synthesised through the citrate-nitrate method.
Titulo: Influence of sintering temperature on the properties of the screen-printed anode of the LSMO4 Ruddlesden-Popper perovskite for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Initially, the characterisation of LSMO4 anode powders was analyzed by X-ray diffraction, field emission scanning electron microscopy (FESEM), and Brunauer-EmmettTeller analysis.
Titulo: Influence of sintering temperature on the properties of the screen-printed anode of the LSMO4 Ruddlesden-Popper perovskite for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Subsequently, an LSMO4 film was screen-printed onto LSGM substrates and sintered at four different temperatures: 1000 degrees C, 1100 degrees C, 1200 degrees C, and 1300 degrees C.
Titulo: Influence of sintering temperature on the properties of the screen-printed anode of the LSMO4 Ruddlesden-Popper perovskite for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of the sintering temperature on the microstructure, electronic conductivity, and electrochemical performance of the screen-printed anode film was analyzed by FESEM, DC 4-point probe method, and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS).
Titulo: Influence of sintering temperature on the properties of the screen-printed anode of the LSMO4 Ruddlesden-Popper perovskite for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The different values of average surface porosities (21-35%) and anode film thickness (14-41 mm) resulting from various sintering temperatures significantly influenced the electronic conductivity and electrochemical performance of the anode films.
Titulo: Influence of sintering temperature on the properties of the screen-printed anode of the LSMO4 Ruddlesden-Popper perovskite for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities of the anode films sintered at 1000 degrees C, 1100 degrees C, 1200 degrees C, and 1300 degrees C were found to be 1.53 S/ cm, 1.95 S/cm, 3.30 S/cm, and 3.73 S/cm at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Influence of sintering temperature on the properties of the screen-printed anode of the LSMO4 Ruddlesden-Popper perovskite for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The activation energy of anodes sintered at 1000-1300 degrees C was in the range of 0.61-0.72 eV.
Titulo: Influence of sintering temperature on the properties of the screen-printed anode of the LSMO4 Ruddlesden-Popper perovskite for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The EIS analysis showed that the LSMO4 anode film sintered at 1000 degrees C possessed the lowest ASR of 1.52 Ucm2 at 800 degrees C under a wet gas mixture environment, 3 vol% H2O -97 vol% (H2: N2 = 10 : 90).
Titulo: Influence of sintering temperature on the properties of the screen-printed anode of the LSMO4 Ruddlesden-Popper perovskite for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
